  shortDescription: "Robert's acoustic guitar, dusty now. He hasn't played in months
    \u2014 his fingers won't cooperate."
  fullStory: Sunday mornings were for music. The whole house would fill with sound.
  marthaContext: Martha misses the music most. She'd hum along from the kitchen.
    The silence in the house now is the loudest thing she's ever heard.
  davidContext: David and Robert used to jam together. David on harmonica, Robert
    on guitar. They were terrible, but it didn't matter.
